      • updateMethod

        public org.eclipse.uml2.uml.NamedElement updateMethod(int position,
                                                      org.eclipse.cdt.core.model.IParent parent,
                                                      String qualifiedName,
                                                      String body,
                                                      org.eclipse.cdt.core.dom.ast.IASTFunctionDeclarator declarator,
                                                      SyncInformation syncInfo)
        Update a method in the model based on the qualified name.
        Parameters:
        position - The position of the method within the file. Used to identify renaming operations
        parent - the CDT parent which is used to get a list of children
        qualifiedName - the qualified name of a method
        body - the method body
        declarator - the declarator for the method
        Returns:
        the operation or the behavior within the model that got updated. The latter is returned in case of behaviors that do not have a specification (e.g. the effect of a transition).

      • getModelOperationFromName

        public org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Operation getModelOperationFromName(String name,
                                                                org.eclipse.cdt.core.model.IParent parent,
                                                                int position)
        Obtain an operation from the model by using the name of a CDT method. If an operation of the given name does not exist, it might indicate that the method has been renamed.
        Parameters:
        name - the operation name within CDT
        parent - the parent of the CDT method within CDT editor model
        position - the position within the other methods. This information is used to locate methods within the model that might have been renamed in the CDT editor.
        Returns:
